<code>pod-mode.el</code> by SteffenSchwigon is a simple mode for editing [[Perl]] "plain old documentation" <code>.pod</code> files, or POD embedded in Perl code.  Get it from

: http://search.cpan.org/~schwigon/pod-mode/

And also in DebianPackage:emacs-goodies-el.

See also:
* PerlPodCoding -- coding system from <code>=encoding</code>
* PerlPodGt -- helpers for <code>C<...></code> forms
* PerlPodPreview -- previewing formatted POD output
* TinyTools -- contains TinyPerl for vieving POD files.
* [https://github.com/sshaw/copy-as-format copy-as-format] -- copy buffer locations as POD formatted code
* [https://github.com/rmloveland/flycheck-pod flycheck-pod] -- flycheck support for POD

